# gen339 — L14 META-REASONING (abstraction-ceiling §1b): thinking about
# thinking as KB knowledge in kb/core/meta.p0. Converse pairs (inverse_of/2),
# the L7 question typology (question_form/2, reachable through the answer_frame
# engine's stopword second pass — interrogatives ARE stopwords), and reasoning
# contrasts (difference_between/3). Each was a measured wall in the gen338
# probe battery. NOTE: relation_type/2 facts also landed, but their chat frame
# («which relations are transitive?») is still walled — the open handoff item.
> what is the inverse of before?
< After.
> what kind of question is "why is the sky blue"?
< A why-question asks for a cause, a reason or a justification.
> what kind of question is "where is paris"?
< A where-question asks for a place or location.
> what is the difference between correlation and causation?
< Correlation means two things vary together; causation means one actually produces the other
> what is the difference between a cause and an enabling condition?
< A cause actively produces the effect; an enabling condition only makes it possible
> what is the difference between deduction and induction?
< Deduction derives what must follow from rules; induction generalizes a rule from examples